CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 7, 1959, pg. 14, reads: "TO PRESENT EASTER CABARET - The Altrusix Club will present its fourth annual Eastereme Cabaret at the Horizon Room, Greater Pittsburgh Airport, on Sunday, March 29, from 10 P.M. until 2 A.M. Featured will be the Bobby Jones combo, dancer Dee Dee Clark and Todd, female impersonator. These young ladies are candidates for "Miss Altrusix."  Front, left to right: Carrie Hauser, Helen Champlin and Patricia Dee.  Rear: Dolores Clark Adel White, Elaine Peoples and Eloise Battles.  Donation is $2.50 per person. For further information, call MU. 1-0380 or PE. 1435 - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of seven young women, candidates for "Miss Altrusix" including seated: Carrie Hauser, Helen Champlin, Patricia Dee; standing: Dolores Clark, Adel White, Elaine Peoples, and Eloise Battles, posed in interior with wood paneling and piano on left, vertical format
